Data Dictionary

FILES FROM PHYSIOLOGICAL SIGNALS

File types
_bp Blood Pressure Arterial blood pressure measured with finapress (finger) _rsp Respiration Respiratory rates and amplitudes measured with two chest bands (abdominal and thoracis) with signals averaged _rtimes Heart Rate Heart rate measured with 3-lead ECG, here each “r waves” is marked (all files manually checked), so the hear rate (beats per minutes) can be computed as the distance (in sec) between each wave divided by 60 (sec) .2.bi Bad Intervals Since the data sometimes contain noise or sections of the files with non-sinus rhythms that cannot be analyzed, there is a “bad interval” file for each period in the protocol in which such unanalyzable data occurred.  These “BI” files are in text format and each line contains the start and stop time of each unscorable interval within each period.  Analyses of data with bad intervals must exclude these portions of the files.  _eda Electrodermal activity EDA or skin conductance measured every 1msec from the left palm. DATA TO COME FROM ELLIE YAN.

VARIABLE DESCRIPTIONS

_bp Name Units pSec Time of systole seconds pVal Pressure at systole mmHg (milliliters of mercury) tSec Time of diatole seconds tVal Pressure at diastole mmHg (milliliters of mercury)

_rsp Name Units pSec Time of peak inspiration seconds pVal Value at peak inspiration mVolts (these should be in liters, will need to use calibration to convert) tSec Time of peak expiration seconds tVal Value at peak expiration mVolts (these should be in liters, will need to use calibration to convert)

_rtimes Name Units pSec Time of each r wave seconds

Periods (in order) Description Duration

Base Baseline, after 25 minutes of resting. 366 seconds Pre First biological samples collected (saliva, blood, temp, affect) [-5min] 300 seconds Instruct Instructions for TSST given by study coordinator Variable duration (about 300 seconds) Prep Task Speech preparation, no pen or paper 122-123 seconds Task Public speech task (Trier social stress task - TSST) 183-184 seconds Post 5 Samples collected 5 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 10 Samples collected 10 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 20 Samples collected 20 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 30 Samples collected 30 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 60 Samples collected 60 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 90 Samples collected 90 minutes post-task 300 seconds Post 120 Samples collected 120 minutes post-task 300 seconds DBT Deep Breathing Task: Paced breathing - inhalation/exhalation 420 seconds ST Sit Stand: Participants go from seated position to standing, remain standing 420 seconds SST Sit Stand Test: Participants repeatedly sit and stand (squats) for 30 secs 420 seconds CP Cold Pressor Task: Participants submerge one hand in ice bath for 90 secs 660 seconds
